  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - MONK</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>MONK PRIDE</font> - <small>Onigami Satsugai, Lanys T'vyl</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>By the time you hit these levels, monks are rarer and rarer. There seems to be more rangers, warriors, and casters around. Monks are less of a novelty, and people were tired of the monk hell levels.
<br><br>
Once you hit 20, theres many many places you can hunt. Some prefer HighKeep, Unrest, South Karana, etc. My personal favorite was Mistmoore, and I'll give reasons why.<br><br>

Most of the other places had slow spawns, or very bad pulls, or very bad slow pulls. Mistmoores balance is that it has the worst trains Ive ever seen in my life. But heres the thing. Monks Love trains! Yeah.. by this time you should have FD to 100-120, and not fail it much at all. So when those huge trains come, you lie there silent, and can tell your groupmates when the train is gone. Besides, you never train, and heres the best part... you are the best puller, ever.
<br><br>
Intro to Feign Death pulls -<br>
feign death rocks for pulling, until level 35 or so.
<br><br>
Theres two types that I practice. If I want 1-3 things to come,(some groups like lots of easy things rather than one big thing) then I do an aggro range pull. This pull consists of running right up to a creature, feigning death, and waiting 10 sec. Once feign death recycles, stand up again and run away. The creature should aggro on you as soon as you hit the circle that is their aggro radius. Aggro radii are not a sphere, but more of a movement detector of a circle around the creature. This should give you a good 5-10 feet between melee range of the creature, and with SoW, you are the pulling machine. Always remember to FD again, if you pull to many.<br><br>

Then there is classic FD pulling, where you get aggrod by any number of things, FD, and change views to watch them run away. They should walk away randomly. Once all of them have left, run and hit the last one. He should aggro on you alone, and the rest should leave you alone. This pull takes tons and tons of practice, and sometimes sneak can help. Groups will love it though, and your enchanter will get bored.
<br><br>
After 25 or so, your on your own for places to hunt. Cazic Thule is decent, as is Mistmoore, South Karana's Paw is still good, you can sometimes get cyclops groups in Rathe mtns.
<br><br>
At around 30, you really start kicking major ass. I've outdamaged warriors by about twofold, and can even occasionally tank. You can get in quad hits, and even quintuplet ones, if you count a special attack. And Flying kick is frikken amazing.
<br><br>
Onigami Satsugai<br>
Monk of the Ashen Order</td></tr>
